{"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"GtkBackend","role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While Gtk isn’t the preferred UI framework on every Linux distro, it’s the closest thing SwiftCrossUI has to a native Linux backend for now. The Qt backend may be brought back to life at some point to cover the rest of Linux distros."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For targetting older pre Gtk 4 Linux distros, see the secondary "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend","isActive":true}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This backend supports Linux, macOS, and Windows, but its support for macOS has a few known issues worse due to underlying Gtk issues (and its support for Windows isn’t well tested)."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"System dependencies","anchor":"System-dependencies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you can use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"text":" you must install the required system dependencies for your platform. Here are installation instructions tailored to each supported platform;","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Linux","anchor":"Linux"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Debian-based distros","sudo apt install libgtk-4-dev clang","","# Fedora-based distros","sudo dnf install gtk4-devel clang"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 1: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"installing the required dependencies on Debian-based and Fedora-based Linux distros","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you run into errors related to not finding ","type":"text"},{"code":"gtk\/gtk.h","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project, try restarting your computer. This has worked in some cases (although there may be a more elegant solution).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are on a non-Debian non-Fedora distro and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" requirements end up differing significantly from the requirements stated above, please open a GitHub issue or PR so that we can improve the documentation."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"macOS","anchor":"macOS"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["brew install pkg-config gtk4"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 2: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"installing the required dependencies using Homebrew","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have Homebrew, installation instructions can be found at ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/brew.sh","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It should also be possible to use "},{"code":"gtk4","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" installed via MacPorts, but I have not tested that."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you run into errors related to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"libffi"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FFI"},{"text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"text":", which can occur when certain older versions of the Xcode Command Line Tools are installed, try running the following command to patch libffi:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["sed -i '' 's\/-I..includedir.\/\/g' $(brew --prefix)\/Library\/Homebrew\/os\/mac\/pkgconfig\/*\/libffi.pc"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 3: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"fixing the ","type":"text"},{"code":"libffi","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" issue that some people face","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Windows","anchor":"Windows"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows things are a bit complicated (as usual), so we only support installation via "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg"},{"type":"text","text":". First, install vcpkg;"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["git clone https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg C:\\vcpkg","C:\\vcpkg\\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 4: "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"install vcpkg (requires git cli)","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It’s important to install vcpkg at the root of a drive due to limitations of the Gtk build system."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Warning","style":"warning"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After installation, make the following changes to your environment variables:"}]}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKG_CONFIG_PATH"},{"text":" environment variable to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\lib\\pkgconfig"},{"text":". This is only required for building.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add "},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to your "},{"code":"Path","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable. This is only required for running."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With vcpkg installed, you have two options for Gtk installation; global installation, and project-local installation"}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Global Gtk 4 installation (recommended)","anchor":"Global-Gtk-4-installation-recommended"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that the command depends on your machine’s architecture; choose between Figure 5 and Figure 6 accordingly.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Installation can take 45+ minutes depending on your machine."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet x64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 5: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install Gtk 4 globally on x64 Windows"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet arm64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 6: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"install Gtk 4 globally on arm64 Windows","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Run the chosen command at the root of your drive to ensure that vcpkg doesn’t run in manifest mode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Warning","style":"warning"},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Project-local Gtk 4 installation (more unreliable)","anchor":"Project-local-Gtk-4-installation-more-unreliable"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the absolute path to your project contains spaces, it is possible that vcpkg will break, and installing globally will be a more reliable strategy.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To install Gtk 4 in a project-local dependency store you must setup a ","type":"text"},{"code":"vcpkg.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" manifest file and then run vcpkg, as detailed below;","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First "},{"code":"vcpkg.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" at the root of your project and make sure that it includes the "},{"code":"gtk","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" dependency as demonstrated in Figure 7."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["{","    \"name\": \"project-name\",","    \"version-string\": \"main\",","    \"dependencies\": [\"gtk\"]","}"],"syntax":"json"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 7: "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"an example "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vcpkg.json"},{"type":"text","text":" package manifest"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install --triplet x64-windows"],"syntax":"sh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 8: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install the dependencies listed in your package manifest"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace the triplet with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arm64-windows"},{"type":"text","text":" if you’re on ARM64"}]}],"name":"Warning","style":"warning"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Usage","anchor":"Usage"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["...","","let package = Package(","  ...","  targets: [","    ...","    .executableTarget(","      name: \"YourApp\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"SwiftCrossUI\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","        .product(name: